Diagnosis. Species in this genus are characterized by (1) frontoparietals, two, (2) supraciliaries, 4–5, (3) supraoculars, four, (4) prefrontal contact, absent (rarely prefrontals in point contact in
Alinea luciae
), (5) parietal contact, present, (6) rows of nuchals, 1–3, (7) dorsals + ventrals, 116–136, (8) total digital lamellae, 231–259, (9) a dark middorsal stripe, absent, (10) dark dorsolateral stripes, absent, (11) a dark lateral stripe, absent (weakly visible, anteriorly, in
A. berengerae
), and (12) dark ventral stripes, present (
A. lanceolata
and
A. luciae
). Maximum body sizes in this genus range from 60–109 mm SVL ( Table 2 ).
